entries.title: Why Are Governors Turning on TikTok?
entries.description: More than 20 states are banning the Chinese-owned app on government devices.

entries.title: Google Critic Cleared to Work on U.S. Antitrust Matters Involving Company
entries.description: The Justice Department cleared its top antitrust official, Jonathan Kanter, to oversee cases and investigations involving the company.

entries.title: YouTube Tests New Hub of Free Streaming Channels
entries.description: The tech company’s effort could rival Roku and Fox in a fast-growing area of streaming business, as it expands its video ambitions.

entries.title: Judge Hears Elon Musk Request to Relocate Trial Over Tesla Tweets
entries.description: A federal judge kicked off a hearing on Elon Musk’s request to relocate a coming securities-fraud trial away from San Francisco.

entries.title: What If Tesla Is…Just a Car Company?
entries.description: Tesla’s aura as an elite tech disrupter dims as EV competitors multiply and improve their offerings. Musk’s messy involvement with Twitter isn’t helping.

entries.title: China Buys Stake in Alibaba Subsidiary
entries.description: China’s internet watchdog takes nominal stake in the company, even as a government investigation into another Alibaba affiliate ends.

entries.title: Without Consciousness, AIs Will Be Sociopaths
entries.description: ChatGPT can carry on a conversation, but the most important goal for artificial intelligence is making it understand what it means to have a mind.

entries.title: Don't Write Off Tesla as America's EV Market Booms
entries.description: Tesla’s price cuts and the chaotic implementation of President Biden’s new tax credits for electric vehicles obscure a bigger picture: The shift to EVs in America is getting serious.

entries.title: Toyota Considers New EV-Dedicated Platform
entries.description: The Japanese auto maker aims to manufacture large volumes of electric vehicles efficiently.

entries.title: Tesla Cuts Prices Across Models Sold in U.S.
entries.description: The move could allow some buyers to qualify for a $7,500 U.S. electric-vehicle tax credit.

entries.title: Apple CEO Tim Cook to Take a 40% Pay Cut This Year
entries.description: The iPhone maker said in a filing that Mr. Cook recommended the reduction

entries.title: Sam Bankman-Fried Says Law Firm Worked Closely With FTX Before Bankruptcy
entries.description: The founder and former chief executive of FTX said Sullivan & Cromwell was one of FTX International’s two primary law firms and was FTX U.S.’s primary law firm before the bankruptcy.
